Step 1: Identify the quick assets (items that can be quickly converted to cash). These include:
• Cash on Hand = 3,057,369.78
• Bank Deposits = 4,292,000.00
• Interest Receivable = 14,575.80
• Accounts Receivable = 2,149,792.45

Step 2: Calculate total quick assets:
 Total Quick Assets = 3,057,369.78 + 4,292,000.00 + 14,575.80 + 2,149,792.45
  = 9,513,738.03

Step 3: Identify the total current liabilities, which is given as:
 Total Current Liabilities = 628,478.02

Step 4: Compute the Quick Ratio:
 Quick Ratio = Total Quick Assets / Total Current Liabilities
  = 9,513,738.03 / 628,478.02
  ≈ 15.14

Thus, the Quick Ratio as of the end of the reporting period is approximately 15.14.
